================================================================================
Third-Party Architectural Attributions
================================================================================

EGBIMOTO's architecture was informed by patterns and approaches from the
following open-source projects. No source code was copied verbatim; these are
acknowledged as design influences:

- rst-c (Revit Ribbon Profile Manager)
  The Bootstrap + side-engine loading pattern (AssemblyDependencyResolver),
  add-in directory scanning, and health snapshot concepts in EGBIMOTO were
  adapted from this project's architecture.

- pyRevit
  The manifest-driven extension model and operation registry concepts drew
  inspiration from pyRevit's approach to Revit automation.

- 460707300-tech/MEPStraighten  (MIT License)
  The double-elbow (S-bend / 翻弯) detection and straightening algorithm in
  MepStraightenOps.cs was adapted from this project. The original single-shot
  PickObject command was reworked into EGBIMOTO's manifest/DAG op model
  (batch scan + report + optional apply). Original copyright belongs to the
  respective author under the MIT License.

- 460707300-tech/MEPRegionMarker
  The "MEP elements inside a closed region" detection approach in
  MepRegionOps.cs was inspired by this project. The interactive region-drawing
  and tagging command was reworked into Room/Area-boundary based counting,
  reporting, and parameter-writing ops.

- 460707300-tech/Arbitrary3D  (MIT License)
  The rectangular duct equivalent-section conversion concept ("风管截面转换")
  listed in this project's MEP tool catalog inspired DuctSectionOps.cs. No code
  was copied; the implementation was written from scratch using ASHRAE
  equivalent-diameter formulas.

- Dave5264/transom-revit
  The schedule round-trip architecture in ScheduleRoundtripOps.cs — the
  "display pass" (reading via ViewSchedule.GetCellText for exact visual fidelity)
  and the "rolled-back UID anchor" pattern (stamp UniqueId, AddField, Regenerate,
  read, then RollBack so the model is never persistently changed) — was learned
  from this project's design docs (SPEC.md, IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md). No code was
  copied; the implementation was written from scratch for EGBIMOTO's manifest/DAG
  op model, limited to the core round-trip scope (non-grouped itemized schedules).
  Transom's product-level features (NPOI style interning, colour contract, grouped
  type-parameter conflict resolution, MCP bridge) are intentionally out of scope.

- sbuchanan01/hanger-layout-for-revit  (MIT License, Autodesk evaluation sample)
  The size-banded hanger spacing concept inspired the data/validation/mep_aski_aralik.json
  ruleset and the place_family_along_mep op. No code was copied; the original targets
  Autodesk Fabrication parts via a modeless dialog, whereas EGBIMOTO implements generic
  point-along-curve family placement for standard Revit MEP (Pipe/Duct/CableTray) driven
  by manifests.

